Library Company, 15. Northern France, Second half 15th century. This manuscript is a twenty-three folio fragment of a fifteenth-century Book of Hours produced in Northern France. It contains fragments of the Seven Penitential Psalms, Hours of the Cross, Hours of the Holy Spirit, and Litany. The first five folios, all singletons, are severely and irregularly trimmed. Apart from three conjoined bifolia, the book consists of bound singletons. The manuscript was bequeathed to the Loganian Library (later the Library Company of Philadelphia) by William Mackenzie.
